snippet.title: AMBER Alert canceled after 3-year-old girl found safe; suspect in custody
snippet.description:
The AMBER Alert for 3-year-old Kaysie Jay Lipscomb has been canceled; officials confirm she is safe. Lipscomb was found in Stallings, North Carolina, with 31-year-old Raheem Tyshawn Pate. 

The Union County Sheriff's Office said Pate has been taken into custody, arrested on unrelated charges.

The Gaston County Police Department is continuing to investigate the AMBER Alert and is expected to release more information as the investigation develops.

https://www.wcnc.com/article/news/local/gastonia/gastonia-amber-alert/275-be29ec3b-725b-4392-871e-e5e44110eb30
